relation: Winners of 9 straight look like the most complete team in the league.
Clinched the NFC North with their 12th straight victory against divisional foes.
Division champions for the second straight season.
Impressively overcame blowing a 28 point second half lead to rally and beat the Patriots.
Handed the Giants their first regular season shutout since '96.
Welker has caught 100 passed in a season for the fifth time, a league record.
Scored 50 for a second consecutive week.
Clinched a playoff spot despite 3 straight losses. Nobody seems to want to claim the sixth seed in the AFC.
Luck trails Newton's rookie passing record of 4051 yards by only 73 yards.
Widely panned decision to take a second rookie QB after RGIII looks brilliant in hindsight.
Winners of 5 of the last 6 now in a 3 way tie atop the division.
Had a long work week to focus on the upcoming critical matchup in Pittsburgh.
Tie breakers mean they could win out and still not get to defend their title.
Purple Jesus is only 294 yards shy of breaking the single season rushing record of 2,105 yards held by Dickerson.
In serious jeopardy of missing the playoffs after beginning the season at 7-1.
Last time they shut out an opponent in New Orleans was '91.
Overachievers have something to build upon.
Newton trying hard to save Rivera's job.
Bradford has been sacked in 30 straight games, the longest active streak in the league.
Freeman threw 4 interceptions in New Orleans after throwing 8 previously for the entire season.
CJ's 94 yard TD run was the longest in franchise history and the longest in the league since '06.
Mercifully eliminated thanks in large part to 5 more turnovers by Dirty Sanchez.
Ended their 9 game losing streak because of the defense and turnover prone Stafford despite Lindley throwing for only 104 yards.
Reaching for the 28 year old Weeden in the first round looks even worse after losing to fourth round backup Cousins.
Norv and Smith are dead men walking.
Appear to have quit on Schwartz.
Fell into a tie for last in scoring defense with Raiders. How can Gailey survive this debacle?
Youngsters simply not prepared for short work week late in the season. Mercifully the Thursday night games are done for the year.
If only they could play the Chiefs every week.
Shut out by the most scored upon defense in the league.
Need to win the final 2 to avoid the worst season in franchise history.
